mod-ui (3.0-7) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Cut web UI startup time from ~7s to under 2s to interactive.
  * Bulk-fetch plugin metadata on pedalboard load: buffer plugins between
    loading_start and loading_end and request them in one POST /effect/bulk/
    call (run in parallel with /snapshot/name) instead of one serial
    GET /effect/get per plugin.
  * Gate non-forced scheduleAdapt calls during pedalboard load so the per-knob
    getAndSetSize bumps can no longer saturate the adapt drain timer, which had
    been delaying /effect/list by ~5s.
  * Drop the "Loading pedalboard..." overlay as soon as the pedalboard is laid
    out, instead of chaining it behind the plugin-browser search render.
  * Cache the EffectList / get_all_plugins() result server-side, invalidated on
    plugin install and removal.
  * Lazy-load plugin thumbnails via IntersectionObserver so the browser no
    longer fetches the entire catalog of PNGs on load.

 -- Cam Gorrie <sastraxi@gmail.com>  Sat, 27 Jun 2026 04:42:52 +0000

mod-ui (3.0-5) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix bypass feedback stall when mod-ui runs in a background browser tab.
    send_output_data_ready is now called for local clients so mod-host does
    not stall its feedback stream waiting for the data_ready handshake.

